OL,3,CScaffolder speaks out about 'life-
OL,4,Cchanging' accident at power station
OL,6,FHe was trapped for 20 minutes and
OL,7,Fspent 4 days in hospital. He can no
OL,8,Flonger work as a scaffolder and has
OL,9,Fbeen diagnosed with PTSD.
OL,11,FMr Dell said the pain was "instant".
OL,13,F"I was just screaming 'get me out' and
OL,14,Fwe couldn't move it."
OL,16,F"Two and a half years since the
OL,17,Faccident, I'm still on anti-
OL,18,Fdepressants. I'm still taking pain
OL,19,Fkillers. I've still got nerve damage,
OL,20,Fso my foot feels like it's burning all
OL,21,Fthe time. I've got a permanent limp.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
